{"hash":"978865659d06e5628677dcfb830940a89565af21","data":{"post":{"title":"Docker Cheat Sheet","date":"July 20, 2021","content":"<p>Show running containers:</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">docker ps</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Show running and stopped containers:</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">docker ps -a</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Start a container</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">docker start my_container</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Stop a container</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">docker stop my_container</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Remove a container</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">docker rm my_container</span></span></code></pre>\n","tags":[{"title":"Linux","path":"/tag/Linux/"},{"title":"Docker","path":"/tag/Docker/"}]}},"context":{}}